From @GenDaveGoldfein hosting Air Chiefs from 11 nations @AFSpace, to chatting w/@AstroHague, to meeting @richardbranson, capping it all off with a successful @SpaceX Falcon Heavy launch from @NASA & @45thSpaceWing! @SecAFOfficialpic.twitter.com/2K8CqjobsT

1115676372272201729.text: It was an honor to speak with Col Nick Hague live from the @Space_Station at the #SpaceSymposium today! Thank you   @AstroHague for joining us.https://twitter.com/AstroHague/status/1115674631158030336 …

1123007091730370560.text: How do @NASA_Astronauts keep their mental health in check while living in space? One way is by looking out the cupola! @AstroHague explains how viewing Earth through the @space_station window helps him stay connected to the ground. #NASASTEMpic.twitter.com/8Mx14NOpeM

1116852056801849345.text: On April 12, 1961 Yuri Gagarin made history when he become the first human to travel in space in his Vostok 1 spacecraft. We keep this photo taped to the wall on @Space_Station to remember and honor his legacy which paved the way for human spaceflight. #CosmonauticsDaypic.twitter.com/aezQ3fIkqY

1120460038827593733.text: As a young boy I remembered looking up to the stars at night in amazement, wondering if a small town kid from Kansas could ever soar that high. Now I am admiring our planet from the greatest vantage point - on @Space_Station. What a special way to celebrate #EarthDaypic.twitter.com/RSJimsOer5

1115674631158030336.text: It was an honor to speak with @AFSpaceCC and all participants attending the #SpaceSynposium today. Thank you to the @usairforce team for helping create opportunities that led me to achieving maximum altitude on @Space_Station. I hope you enjoyed my microgravity tricks!pic.twitter.com/f8EsjfEb8I

1118524007089954816.text: Will 2019 be a big year for the 2013 astronaut class? Signs point to yes. Congratulations to my 8ball classmates on their recent mission assignments! Looking forward to contributing to space exploration with my good friends and colleagues on @Space_Station.pic.twitter.com/spfxVtz373

1114297448044867590.text: A long week of hard work and spacewalk prep calls for a pizza party. Making pizza in space is similar to making pizza on Earth, the only difference is our ovens look a little different and our pizza can float! Anyone on Earth having pizza tonight?pic.twitter.com/s8459Lcnlq

1118246253110996992.text: It was a pleasure to speak with the hardworking students from various schools in Park County, CO today via HAM radio. Glad I could contribute to your STEAM curriculum - keep up the good work and dream big!https://twitter.com/CBSDenver/status/1117955532537487362 …

1118520433169580038.text: Christina is an amazing crewmate and team member up here, and I couldn’t think of a better person to spend a year on @Space_Station. She’s reliable, prepared and she will be great!https://twitter.com/Astro_Christina/status/1118491046038646784 …

1113973472844238850.text: A visitor arrived at @Space_Station today...the progress resupply vehicle made record timing as it launched and docked to the station in under three and a half hours. Pretty impressive!pic.twitter.com/S6Zy9daF04

1123297934890684417.text: Last week @AstroAnnimal & I prepared 3 new sample containers to be installed outside @Space_Station. The Materials ISS Experiment Flight Facility exposes these samples to the harsh environment of space so that stronger materials can be developed on Earth.pic.twitter.com/oPHDO8F2Ou

1118294390575910912.text: Staying busy on @Space_Station! I recently replaced an igniter in the Advanced Combustion via Microgravity Experiment (ACME), a set of 5 studies of gaseous flames conducted in the Combustion Integrated Rack (CIR) - allowing us to perform combustion experiments in microgravity.pic.twitter.com/TH24MVrAkM

1115059821206802438.text: What does a spacewalk feel like? It’s tough work! It’s the equivalent of running a marathon – you’re in a spacesuit for nearly 12 hours straight with only 32 ounces of water. Watch @AstroAnnimal & @Astro_DavidS perform power upgrades to station tomorrow at 6:30 a.m. on @NASA TVpic.twitter.com/vRu2SjURtr
